# BMC Helix Innovation Studio â€” UI Development Rules

When creating or modifying Angular/TypeScript files in this project, follow these rules:

## Mandatory Reading Before Code Changes

1. **Cookbook**: Read `cookbook/09-best-practices.md` for Angular 18 coding standards
2. **Component structure**: Read `cookbook/02-ui-view-components.md` for the 10-file pattern
3. **After changes**: Run through `cookbook/10-checklists.md` (View Component Review Checklist)

## Critical Rules

- Use `standalone: true` for all components
- Use `ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush`
- Use `@if`/`@for`/`@switch` (NOT `*ngIf`/`*ngFor`)
- Escape `@` as `&#64;` in HTML templates
- Use `RxLogService` instead of `console.log`
- Use `takeUntil(this.destroyed$)` for all subscriptions
- Localize all strings via `localized-strings.json` + `TranslateService`
- Use Adapt components for UI (not raw HTML controls)

## View Component Properties

- **No default values for `title`**: The `title` property in design models (`initialComponentProperties` and `getInitialProperties`) must default to `''` (empty string), NOT a hardcoded label. The view designer user sets the title explicitly. Do NOT use fallback strings like `{{ state?.title || 'Some Title' }}` in templates â€” use `{{ state?.title }}` instead.
- Apply the same rule to any user-facing label property â€” let the view designer control the text.

## Adapt Button (`adapt-button`)

- Use `[btn-type]` for button style, NOT `[variant]`. Supported values: `'primary'`, `'secondary'`, `'tertiary'`, `'toolbar'`, `'success'`, `'info'`, `'warning'`, `'critical'`, `'special'`.
- There is NO `[iconLeft]`, `[iconRight]`, or `[iconOnlyButton]` input. These are silently ignored.
- Add icons as child `<span>` elements with `d-icon-left-{name}` CSS class: `<span class="d-icon-left-pencil"></span>`.
- Valid icon names: `plus`, `pencil`, `trash`, `refresh`, `cross`, `home`, `office_room`, etc. (full list in `@bmc-ux/dpl-iconfont`).
- `d-icon-left-add` does NOT exist â€” use `d-icon-left-plus` instead.

## Adapt Select (`adapt-rx-select`)

- Use **plain string arrays** as `[options]`, NOT `{ name, value }` objects. The default `optionFormatter` calls `.toString()` on each option, so objects display as `[object Object]`.
- Correct: `statuses = ['Enabled', 'Disabled'];`
- Wrong: `statuses = [{ name: 'Enabled', value: 'Enabled' }];`
- If you need `{ name, value }` objects, you MUST also provide `[optionFormatter]="opt => opt.name"`.

## Selection Field Display

- AR System selection fields (like Status) return **numeric values** (0, 1, 2...) from the DataPage API, not display text.
- Use `FoundationService.resolveSelectionValue(formName, fieldId, rawValue)` to map numeric IDs to display names.
- The mapping comes from the record definition's `optionNamesById` property, cached by `FoundationService`.

## Date Formatting

- AR System timestamps may be in epoch seconds OR epoch milliseconds depending on the API.
- Use `FoundationService.formatDate(timestamp)` which auto-detects the format (values > 10^12 = milliseconds, otherwise seconds).

## Component Type String

Must be identical in: registration `type`, `@RxViewComponent({ name })`, and `selector`:
```
<application-name>-<application-name>-<component-name>
```

## Integration Checklist

After creating a component:
- [ ] Import registration module in `<application-name>.module.ts`
- [ ] Export registration module in `index.ts`
- [ ] Verify cross-file consistency (type string, property names)

